quran[13]{c,v,t}:
  21,45,"Tell them, \"I am warning you on the authority of Revelation,\" but the deaf choose not to listen the call when they are warned"
  21,46,"Yet even if a breath from the Wrath of your Lord was to touch them, they will certainly say, \"Woe to us! No doubt we were wrongdoers"
  21,47,"On the Day of Judgement We shall set up scales of justice so that no one will be dealt with unjustly in any way; even if someone has an act as small as a grain of a mustard seed, We will bring it to account, and sufficient are We to settle the accounts"
  21,48,"Certainly, We granted to Moses and Haroon (Aaron) the Criterion of right and wrong, a light and a reminder for those righteous people"
  21,49,"who fear their Lord though they have not seen Him, and dread the Day of Judgment"
  21,50,And now We have revealed this blessed Reminder (The Qurâ€™an). Will you then deny it
  21,51,"Even before that We blessed Abraham with rectitude, for We knew him well"
  21,52,"Remember that occasion when Abraham asked his father and his people, \"What are these images to which you are so devoted"
  21,53,"They replied, \"We found our forefathers worshipping them"
  21,54,"He said \"Then certainly both you and your forefathers have been in manifest error"
  21,55,"They asked, \"Have you brought us the Truth or are you one of the triflers"
  21,56,"He replied, \"Nay! Your Lord is the Lord of the heavens and the earth. It is He Who has created them; and I am of those who bear witness to this"
  21,57,By Allah! I will certainly plan against your idols when you turn and go away